  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "MPEG-1/2 start code structure: all MPEG elements begin with start code prefix 0x000001 + stream_id (1B). Key start codes: 0xB3=sequence_header, 0xBA=pack_header (PS), 0xB8=GOP, 0xB0=user_data, 0xB5=extension, 0x00=picture_header, 0x01-0xAF=slice_start. Sequence Header body (starts at byte 4): horizSize(12b,big) + vertSize(12b,big) + aspectRatio(4b) + frameRate(4b) + bitRate×400(18b) + markerBit(1b) + vbvBufferSize×16KB(10b) + constrainedParams(1b) + loadIntraMatrix(1b). MPEG-2 adds extension start codes (0xB5) after sequence header with profile/level information. MPEG-2 profiles: Simple, Main, High. MPEG-2 levels: Low (352×288), Main (720×576), High-1440, High (1920×1080).",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Check start code at offset 0: 0x000001B3 (seq header) or 0x000001BA (PS pack)",
      "For 0x000001B3: read horizSize (bits 23-12 at offset 4) and vertSize (bits 11-0)",
      "Read frame rate code (bits 3-0 of byte 7): 3=25fps/4=29.97fps/5=30fps",
      "MPEG-2: check for 0x000001B5 extension start code after sequence header for profile/level"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "VLC media player",
    "FFmpeg (mpeg1video/mpeg2video codec)",
    "HandBrake",
    "DVD players (MPEG-2)",
    "DVB-T/DVB-S set-top boxes (MPEG-2 TS)"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Video",
    "extensions": [".mpg", ".mpeg", ".m2v", ".m1v"],
    "relatedFormats": ["TS", "VOB", "MP4"],
    "note": "MPEG-1 (ISO 11172) introduced the 0x000001 start code architecture. MPEG-2 (ISO 13818) extended it with profile/level and interlaced support. MPEG-2 elementary streams (.m2v) are used in DVD-Video (wrapped in Private Stream 1 PES packets). Transport Streams (.ts) carry MPEG-2 video in 188-byte packets with sync byte 0x47."
  },
